/image-to-base64?utm_source=github.com&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=renanbastos93/image-to-base64&amp;utm_campaign=Badge_Grade)\r\n<a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/vue\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/npm/l/vue.svg\" alt=\"License\"></a>\r\n\r\n[npm-image]: https://img.shields.io/npm/v/image-to-base64.svg\r\n[npm-url]: https://npmjs.org/package/image-to-base64\r\n[downloads-image]: https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/image-to-base64.svg\r\n[downloads-url]: https://npmjs.org/package/image-to-base64\r\n\r\n## About\r\nIt's a thing you can use in many situations, for example you can just save the base64 string in your database and increment it in the front-end with the `<img>` tag in HTML.\r\n\r\n## Getting Started\r\nInstallation:\r\n```bash\r\nnpm i -S image-to-base64\r\n```\r\nCode Example:\r\n```js\r\nconst imageToBase64 = require('image-to-base64');\r\n//or\r\n//import imageToBase64 from 'image-to-base64/browser';\r\n\r\nimageToBase64(\"path/to/file.jpg\") // Path to the image\r\n    .then(\r\n        (response) => {\r\n            console.log(response); // \"cGF0aC90by9maWxlLmpwZw==\"\r\n        }\r\n    )\r\n    .catch(\r\n        (error) => {\r\n            console.log(error); // Logs an error if there was one\r\n        }\r\n    )\r\n```\r\nRemember that you can also use an image URL as a parameter.\r\n\r\nCode Example:\r\n```js\r\nimageToBase64(\"https://whatever-image/\") // Image URL\r\n    .then(\r\n        (response) => {\r\n            console.log(response); // \"iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSwCAIA...\"\r\n        }\r\n    )\r\n    .catch(\r\n        (error) => {\r\n            console.log(error); // Logs an error if there was one\r\n        }\r\n    )\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Browser Usage\r\nYou can import image-to-base64 using the `<script>` tag in HTML.\r\n\r\nCode Example:\r\n```html\r\n<script src=\"node_modules/image-to-base64/image-to-base64.min.js\"></script>\r\n```\r\nNow you can use the module normally as in the JS examples above, but you can only use a URL and not a path. \r\n\r\n### LICENSE\r\n[MIT](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT) © 2017 RENAN.BASTOS\r\n","maintainers":[{"name":"robsongajunior","email":"robson.ga.junior@gmail.com"},{"name":"renanbastos93","email":"renanbastos.tec@gmail.com"}],"time":{"modified":"2023-07-16T16:46:51.113Z","created":"2017-10-27T20:42:56.042Z","1.0.0":"2017-10-27T20:42:56.042Z","1.0.1":"2017-10-28T03:13:24.176Z","1.1.0":"2017-11-01T16:34:39.766Z","1.2.0":"2018-02-09T00:53:03.586Z","1.3.0":"2018-02-15T15:08:09.695Z","1.3.1":"2018-03-21T04:08:26.068Z","1.3.5":"2018-03-26T01:58:12.253Z","2.0.0":"2018-09-21T23:17:04.122Z","2.0.1":"2018-09-21T23:28:04.814Z","2.1.0":"2020-05-02T06:30:57.654Z","2.1.1":"2020-07-22T16:39:00.783Z","2.2.0":"2021-04-09T18:22:19.989Z"},"homepage":"https://github.com/renanbastos93/image-to-base64#readme","keywords":["node","nodejs","module convert base64 nodejs","image2base64","image-to-base64","convert-image-base64","convert","save","code","base64","image","webpack","loader","img","src","img src"],"repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/renanbastos93/image-to-base64.git"},"author":{"name":"Renan Bastos -","email":"renanbastos.tec@gmail.com"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/renanbastos93/image-to-base64/issues"},"license":"MIT","readmeFilename":"README.md","users":{"renanbastos93":true,"flumpus-dev":true}}